{"key":"processedPost-6083555","value":{"id":6083555,"first":6083167,"last":6083555,"when":1158800453,"utime":"09/21/06 04:00 AM","content":"You don't want to keep any tray with green molds in your grow area for even one minute after you discover it.  Take it outside and put it in the shade.<br />You want to clone onto agar so you can isolate away from contaminants.  Simply tear a stem lengthwise into two halves, then use a sterile razor or scalpel to scrape a bit of mycelium from the center of the stem that hasn't ever been exposed to the outside air.<br />Personally, I wouldn't clone from a tray with contaminants.  Wait until you get a nice flush with lots of large clusters, then clone from one of the most aggressive clusters.<br />RR","title":"Re: Cloning question"}}